## Performance Tips

### 1. Use Indexes

```typescript
// Firebase Console → Firestore → Indexes
// Create composite indexes for common queries
```

### 2. Limit Query Results

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Paginate large datasets
const q = query(collection(db, 'items'), limit(20));

// ❌ BAD: Load everything
const q = query(collection(db, 'items')); // Could be thousands
```

### 3. Cache Strategy

```typescript
// Get from cache first, then server
import { getDocFromCache, getDocFromServer } from 'firebase/firestore';

async function getCachedDocument(docRef: DocumentReference) {
  try {
    const doc = await getDocFromCache(docRef);
    return doc;
  } catch (e) {
    // Not in cache, fetch from server
    return await getDocFromServer(docRef);
  }
}
```

